                    EARTH SCIENCE > TERRESTRIAL HYDROSPHERE > SURFACE WATER > FLOODS

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    The condition that occurs when water overflows the natural or
artificial confines of a stream or other body of water, or accumulates by
drainage over low-lying areas. 
                
                

                

                
